1939;;Charlie Chan in Reno;;American;;Norman Foster;;Sidney Toler, Ricardo Cortez, Phyllis Brooks, Slim Summerville;;crime;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charlie_Chan_in_Reno;;Mary Whitman has arrived in Reno to obtain a divorce. While there, she is arrested on suspicion of murdering a fellow guest at her hotel (which specializes in divorcers).<br><br>There are many others at the hotel who wanted the victim out of the way. Charlie Chan travels from his home in Honolulu to Reno to solve the murder at the request of Mary's soon-to-be ex-husband.